findStrings.find: final_reduce_list_tracker = [] # record partition ids that already started final reduce

task.summary: Framework for scheduler; merge map result locally.

Fix early file fetch bug This happens when some datanode has not finished local map merge while others have. Then when receiving file request, the target merged file may not be ready. Solved by sending local map merge done json to namenode from each datanode, though schedule plans may be ready, they are not sent to datanodes until local map merge is done on all datanodes.
Add local reduce logic When the client submits a job, it should specifies the schedule plan. Currently HADOOP and ICPP have been fully implemented.

Add logic for revised schedule strategy Final reduce now runs in a separate thread; local reduce no longer overwrites original file; choose locally reduced file during final merging before final reduce.

Missing file request bug fixed. Bug: in thread_shuffle_task, not all partitions in the shuffle_task_list are requested. Reason: in python, params are passed by reference, remove final reduce thread will affect the list in the shuffle thread. Solution: copy list before passing; use counter in final reduce thread.
Specify schedule plan as parameters when running client
In the new plan, final reduce happens with fully shuffle of some partition.
